Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Composer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/composer-6-7)

The integrated AI tool allows you to generate text and images directly in Doxee Composer, as well as translate, summarize and rephrase text. Instructions can be typed into a chat field, and the generated content will be displayed as replies, which can be copied and pasted, or modified with further AI prompts.

Doxee Composer integrates several of the most advanced AI engines currently on the market:

- **Open AI **(ChatGPT): Supports text and image generation. 

[https://openai.com/](https://openai.com/)

- **Mistral AI**: Supports text generation.

[https://mistral.ai/](https://mistral.ai/)

- **DeepL AI**: Translations only.

[https://www.deepl.com/](https://www.deepl.com/)

- **Gemini AI**: Supports text generation.

[https://gemini.google.com/](https://gemini.google.com/)

- **Azure OpenAI**: Supports text and image generation.

[https://azure.microsoft.com/products/ai-services/openai-service](https://azure.microsoft.com/products/ai-services/openai-service)

All providers support standard text and code generation within the chat interface. In addition to that, some providers also support image generation (see [Generate Images](/doxee-platform/docs/ai-assistance-1#generate-images)). The main difference between the AI engines is their training, which affects their output as well as the "tone" of their replies.

> The availability of individual AI engines is dependent on server configuration.

## User Interface
AI Assistance is available directly from the Editor view.

Click the **AI Assistance **tab in the right panel menu or use the keyboard shortcut **Alt + Shift + C **to open the window.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI Assistance tab*

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI providers drop-down menu*

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI providers list*

There are two working modes for AI Assistance:

- Write a free-form prompt in the chat field, e.g. to generate text or images,

- or range-select context within the Editor and use the AI engine to modify it, e.g. to summarize, rephrase or translate text.

> When executing a prompt for range-selected text, the AI engine will try to consider the document structure and styles, if possible. However, this can be tricky with complex structures, and the results might be unexpected if the prompt contains typos or errors or is not worded precisely enough.

## Free-Form Text Prompts
You can use AI Assistance to ask questions or generate content, e.g. business letters, formatted tables, code snippets, or images. This can be pasted directly into the document.

- Type your prompt in the chat field and press *Enter *or click the *Send *button. Be specific and include as many details as possible. You may have to try different wordings to get the best results. Typos and errors may influence the accuracy of the generated content.

The generated content will be displayed as replies in the chat window.

- Click the *Copy *or *Paste *icons in the top right corner of the reply to copy the generated content to your clipboard or paste it directly into the Editor.

When pasting formatted content, you have the option to retain either just structure, or both structure and formatting.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*AI input prompt without context*

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI Copy or Paste Response*

### Generate Images
Some AI engines are capable of generating images based on natural language prompts. These are generated as replies in the chat window and can be pasted into the document.

- To generate images, select an image-capable AI engine from the drop-down menu of available providers and select the **Return images **checkbox. Leaving it unselected will return text-only replies.

- Describe what you want the image to look like. Be specific and include as many details as possible. You may have to generate several images and try different wordings to get the best result. Typos and errors may influence the accuracy of the generated image.

- Click the *Paste *icon to paste the generated content directly into the document.

- If necessary, adjust the image quality in the pop-up menu. Click the *Done *button.

You can now edit the image properties under the **Style **&gt; **Images **tab in the right panel menu (see [Image Element](/doxee-platform/docs/image-element-1)).

> Inserting a lot of images will increase the ITX file size and might slow down your device. It is recommended you save generated images locally.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI image generation*

> Images are not stored within your active chat after a page refresh. They will show up as a placeholder message: "[  Image was removed  ]".

## Range-Selected Context Prompts
You can range-select (highlight) text in the Editor and modify it with AI Assistance. This is useful for working with large portions of text without having to paste it into the chat field manually.

- Hightlight existing text in the Editor.

- Type your prompt in the chat field and press *Enter *or click the *Send *button. Be specific and include as many details as possible. You may have to try different wordings to get the best results. Typos and errors may influence the accuracy of the generated content.

The modified content will be displayed as replies in the chat window. The original context will be displayed in a collapsible area underneath your prompt message.

### Quick Actions
Quick action buttons are available in range-selected context mode and are useful for pre- defined actions that dont require further specification:

- Translate to English, German, Italian

- Rephrase the text

- Summarize the text

- Custom prompt: Type a text prompt into the chat field. The highlighted text will serve as range-selected context.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*AI quick actions in chat window*

*![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)*

*AI quick actions in floating toolbar*

> Using the quick action buttons will immediately overwrite any highlighted text in the Editor with the modified content. The original styles and properties are kept, if possible.

> The maximum length of the generated response depends on the server configuration max_tokens. If the request exceeds this resource configuration, an incomplete response will be generated. Using the quick action buttons may result in loss of content when the response is inserted into the template.

## Modifying AI Responses
You can apply quick actions to responses in the AI chat window, without the need to highlight text first. This allows you to further modify AI-generated content before inserting it into the document.

Click the three-dot context menu icon and choose one of the pre-defined quick actions, or type a custom prompt in the chat field.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI context menu*

*Custom prompt *can be used to specify requests, e.g. to translate to another language or to define the tone of a rephrased text. The response will be displayed in the chat window and can be modified further.

## DeepL User Interface
The DeepL chat interface differs slightly from the general [User Interface](/doxee-platform/docs/ai-assistance-1#user-interface):

- The drop-down menus **Source language **and **Target language **appear at the top of the chat window.

- With range-selected context in the Editor,

the chat field is replaced by a **Translate selection **button

- and the pre-defined [Quick Actions](/doxee-platform/docs/ai-assistance-1#quick-actions) disappear from the floating toolbar.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI DeepL user interface*

- **Source language **can be chosen from the drop-down menu or detected automatically.

- **Target language **can be chosen from the drop-down menu or detected automatically based on the current app language.

To switch the source and target languages, click the *Switch languages *icon in-between the drop-down menus:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*AI DeepL model language switch*

> Using the **Translate selection **button will immediately overwrite any highlighted text in the Editor with the modified content. The original styles and properties are kept, if possible.

## Saved Chats
You can chat with an unlimited number of AI engines at the same time in a single document editor. Organize ongoing chats in the Chat history drop-down menu.

To start a new AI chat, open the **Chat history **drop-down menu underneath the text field and click *Start new chat*. An empty chat will open in the AI Assistance tab.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*AI multiple chats*

The context of the chat is preserved across AI providers. You can start with one AI provider and then switch to another in the same saved chat, continuing to give prompts while maintaining the context.

Rename or delete chats by clicking the pencil or trashcan icons.

Adjust how many messages are saved in the chat after a page refresh by clicking the cog icon on the bottom right and typing the number in the numerical field. Set the number of saved chat messages to 0 if you want to clear an active chat after every page refresh.

> You have to adjust this setting separately for every saved chat. By default, the number is set to 10. This includes both your messages and the AI engines replies (including image placeholder messages). Any messages exceeding that number will be deleted after a page refresh, starting with the oldest.

> Images are not stored within your active chat after a page refresh. They will show up as a placeholder message: "[  Image was removed  ]". It is recommended you save generated images locally.

Clear active chat history manually by clicking the eraser icon.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

*AI chat settings*

## AI Assistance Configuration
If a particular AI provider is not configured, it cannot be selected from the drop-down menu of providers.

If the server configuration of AI Assistance is not set up, or unavailable, an error message is displayed:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

*AI chat configuration error message*

> Server configuration is probably missing. Please contact your server administrator (see also Admin Guide).
